title: Grateful Dead Live at Compton Terrace Amphitheatre on 1992-12-06
description: Here Comes Sunshine, Greatest Story Ever Told, Friend Of The Devil, Me & My Uncle-> Maggie's Farm, Althea, When I Paint My Masterpiece, Deal Samson & Delilah, Crazy Fingers-> Uncle John's Band-> Jam-> Playin' In The Band Reprise-> Drums-> Jam-> The Last Time-> China Doll-> Throwing Stones, Not Fade Away, E: Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text: Sunshine One of the nice breakout shows of 92.

Here Comes Sunshine Flew into a wet and flooded Arizona from a drizzley Oregon. Was worried about the shows ability to sustain an audience as to the concept of whether weather. Sun came out Sat morning on cue, cruised to show. No better opening than HERE COMES SUNSHINE. Hooked up with folks to scam out of the lot fee and park in an adjoining field for Sunday's show. They lead the pack into the spot and became windows high swamped in mud sand sagebrush. Arrived in full mud camo overlay to the tie dies. Another show, another 100 stories.
Someone brough a cat to the show I remember being out of my mind between sets and having some woman walk be with a cat in her jacket.  Weird.
